         <abstract id="aspace_62ac0ff7495e6e83d4dbf4b1ac993975">Theordore C. Ruch, physiologist and primatologist, received his Ph.D. at Yale in physiology in 1933. The collection contains both sides of the correspondence between Ruch and his mentor, John F. Fulton, as well as related correspondence to/from Ruch or Fulton and others. Subjects include the publishing of Ruch's <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
               <part>Bibliographia primatologica</part>
            </title> in 1941, Ruch's work with Fulton on editions of William Henry Howell's <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
               <part>Textbook of Physiology</part>
            </title>, and the organization of physiology at Washington University, where Ruch became department chairman, and at Yale.</abstract>
