               <scopecontent id="aspace_da4c41e01788a3e77344ac4151e4e099">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>List of section editors, instructions for section editors, and section outlines.</p>
                  <p>William Henry Howell, a physiologist at Johns Hopkins, published the first edition of this text under the title <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
                        <part>Text-book of physiology,</part>
                     </title>in 1905. Fourteen editions were edited by Howell, who died in 1940. Fulton took on the task of editing the 15th edition which appeared as <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
                        <part>Howell's Textbook of Physiology</part>
                     </title> (Philadelphia: Saunders, 1946). Ruch wrote the section on sensation consisting of several chapters.</p>
               </scopecontent>
