               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_4ed3aed2426ce0125557bc8fc81782de">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>26 leaves. Fulton describes the organization of the department, the facilities of the Laboratory of Physiology, and his plans for medical education and training of graduate students. He complains about the excessive amount of administrative and committee work. This is a carbon copy presumably given to Ruch, who was a graduate student at the time.</p>
               </scopecontent>
